children.text: There are screws installed through the top of the parapet wall in this balcony, which may lead to leaking and damage to the building elements.
Part 3.8.1.3 - External above ground membranes of the NCC’s Building Code of Australia requires that
‘Waterproofing membranes for external above ground use must comply with AS 4654.1 and AS 4654.2’

, and the relevant Australian Standard AS 4654.2 Waterproofing membranes for external above-ground use is clear that screws must not be installed through the parapet, and instead provides a detail on how this must be installed, see below;
As the current detail may result in future leaking, this balcony will need to be properly rectified by replacing the balcony parapet detail in accordance with the BCA and AS4654.
